-- Peru Stocks: Alturas, Candente, Minera IRL, Panoro, Rio Alto
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-23T17:04:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/peru-stocks-alturas-candente-minera-irl-panoro-rio-alto.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:23 a.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  gained for the fifth session in six,
rising 0.8 percent to 21,048.98. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD) 
climbed 0.6 percent to 2,696.85.  Copper and gold miners surged after the metals advanced in
 New York  and  London , said Eduardo Fernandini, a trader at Lima-
based brokerage Kallpa Securities SAB.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 10 percent to 11 cents.  Panoro
Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold exploration
company, jumped 8.8 percent to 62 cents.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT) 
, a Canadian exploration company, gained 3.9 percent to
$1.06.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
advanced 1.9 percent to $3.73 after appointing former Volcan
Cia. Minera SAA executive Victor Gobitz as chief operating
officer.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer
with a gold mine in Peru, rose 1.8 percent to $1.12.  Southern
Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peruâ€™s biggest copper producer, climbed
1.4 percent to $35.80. The company is expected to publish
fourth-quarter earnings this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
